For **tight bound (Î˜)**, you need **any** two positive constants $c_1$ and $c_2$ (with $c_1 < c_2$) such that:

$$
c_1 n \;\le\; f(n) \;\le\; c_2 n \quad \text{for all } n \ge n_0
$$

Thereâ€™s no requirement that you *must* use 2 and 3.
We picked 2 and 3 because they are the simplest values around the coefficient of the leading term (2).

